Comment: 0,0:00:13.36,0:00:15.20,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Snails and cows ^_^
Dialogue: 6,0:00:02.17,0:00:03.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lost cow.
Dialogue: 6,0:00:04.92,0:00:06.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's gotta be "lost cow".
Dialogue: 6,0:00:06.73,0:00:10.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The kanji for "cow" is part of how you write "snail", right?
Dialogue: 6,0:00:10.25,0:00:13.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take the "whirl" out of "whirlpool", replace the radical for "water" with the one for "bug", then follow it with "cow".
Dialogue: 6,0:00:13.78,0:00:15.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you get "snail".
Dialogue: 6,0:00:15.55,0:00:20.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a large numbers of oddities that lead humans astray.
Dialogue: 6,0:00:20.52,0:00:25.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if it's that type and she calls it a snail, it has to be a lost cow.
Dialogue: 6,0:02:40.36,0:02:41.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was right here.
Dialogue: 6,0:02:42.77,0:02:46.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The house I lived in was right here.
Dialogue: 6,0:02:46.89,0:02:50.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"House"... That's a street.
Dialogue: 6,0:02:50.44,0:02:52.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Urban renewal, huh. 
Dialogue: 6,0:02:52.24,0:02:55.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And to think that it's been less than a year.
Dialogue: 6,0:02:58.43,0:03:02.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We sold it, so I didn't really expect it to still be here
Dialogue: 6,0:03:02.88,0:03:04.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it still leaves me feeling pretty blue.
Dialogue: 6,0:03:04.91,0:03:06.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I guess.
Dialogue: 6,0:03:09.03,0:03:12.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm wasting your time crying over spilt milk.
Dialogue: 6,0:03:12.35,0:03:14.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Araragi-kun.
Dialogue: 6,0:03:14.78,0:03:15.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You okay?
Dialogue: 6,0:03:15.75,0:03:17.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine.
Dialogue: 6,0:03:17.31,0:03:18.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 6,0:03:18.46,0:03:19.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Hachikuji.
Dialogue: 6,0:03:19.90,0:03:31.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{note music}
Dialogue: 6,0:03:31.86,0:03:36.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Hachikuji, back off a little. You're making it hard to walk.
Dialogue: 6,0:03:37.42,0:03:39.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, say something. Don't just stand there.
Dialogue: 6,0:03:39.38,0:03:43.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like I'm firmly attached to your leg!
Dialogue: 6,0:03:43.95,0:03:46.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're horrible! I'm telling the PTA on you!
Dialogue: 6,0:03:47.14,0:03:48.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The PTA?
Dialogue: 6,0:03:48.29,0:03:50.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The PTA is an amazing organization!
Dialogue: 6,0:03:50.92,0:03:55.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Araragi-san, you're just an underage civilian with no authority!
Dialogue: 6,0:03:55.66,0:03:58.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They'll lay you flat with a fingertip! 
Dialogue: 6,0:03:59.07,0:04:01.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With just a fingertip? Sounds scary.
Dialogue: 6,0:04:01.98,0:04:05.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Hachikuji, what does PTA stand for?
Dialogue: 6,0:04:05.30,0:04:06.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, umm...
Dialogue: 6,0:04:06.97,0:04:11.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,PTA is an abbreviation for "Parent-Teacher Association".
Dialogue: 6,0:04:11.82,0:04:13.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It means a group formed between parents and teachers.
Dialogue: 6,0:04:14.70,0:04:19.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's also an abbreviation for the medical term "percutaneous transluminal angioplasty".
Dialogue: 6,0:04:20.75,0:04:27.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think that's what you need, so it must be Parent-Teacher Association. 
Dialogue: 6,0:04:28.19,0:04:30.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know everything, don't you, Senjougahara?
Dialogue: 6,0:04:30.49,0:04:33.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that way because you're unlearned and incapable.
Dialogue: 6,0:04:33.86,0:04:37.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't mind being called unlearned, it has a nice ring to it.
Dialogue: 6,0:04:37.42,0:04:39.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But isn't it uncalled for to say I'm incapable over that?
Dialogue: 6,0:04:39.80,0:04:43.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it? Then I'll call you miserable instead. {note hisai->hisan pun}
Dialogue: 6,0:04:52.37,0:04:53.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Hachikuji.
Dialogue: 6,0:04:53.83,0:04:55.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What, Araragi-san?
Dialogue: 6,0:04:55.71,0:04:58.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just what's at this address?
Dialogue: 6,0:05:00.57,0:05:03.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not talking! I plead the Fifth! 
Dialogue: 6,0:05:04.24,0:05:06.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't tell me, I ain't gonna take you there.
Dialogue: 6,0:05:06.55,0:05:09.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like I asked you to! I can go alone!
Dialogue: 6,0:05:09.07,0:05:10.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you're lost, aren't you?
Dialogue: 6,0:05:10.70,0:05:11.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what?!
Dialogue: 6,0:05:13.84,0:05:16.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well... Uh, Hachikuji?
Dialogue: 6,0:05:16.19,0:05:20.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For future reference, it's best to ask someone for help when that happens.
Dialogue: 6,0:05:20.86,0:05:24.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I'd do that if I was like you and didn't believe in myself.
Dialogue: 6,0:05:24.93,0:05:27.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can ask people for things until you feel satisfied.
Dialogue: 6,0:05:27.23,0:05:30.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I feel no need to do that.
Dialogue: 6,0:05:30.17,0:05:34.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For me, this is just like using an everyday vending machine!
Dialogue: 6,0:05:35.41,0:05:36.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sale at a fixed price, huh.
Dialogue: 6,0:05:37.58,0:05:39.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Understood, young lady..
Dialogue: 6,0:05:39.98,0:05:45.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, inform me if there is anything I should know about this address.
Dialogue: 6,0:05:45.43,0:05:47.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't sound very sincere.
Dialogue: 6,0:05:49.56,0:05:53.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That would've been good enough to coax the truth out of either of my sisters.
Dialogue: 6,0:05:53.44,0:05:57.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't treat Hachikuji like she's just a stupid kid.
Dialogue: 6,0:05:57.36,0:05:59.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, what do I do.
Dialogue: 6,0:06:00.54,0:06:02.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Young lady, I'll give you an allowance.
Dialogue: 6,0:06:03.36,0:06:04.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell you anything!
Dialogue: 6,0:06:04.76,0:06:05.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's just a stupid kid.
Dialogue: 6,0:06:08.25,0:06:11.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone named Tsunade-san lives there.
Dialogue: 6,0:06:14.57,0:06:16.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know them?
Dialogue: 6,0:06:16.28,0:06:17.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's a relative.
Dialogue: 6,0:06:17.43,0:06:22.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shouldn't you be at home showing some respect for your family on Mother's Day?
Dialogue: 6,0:06:22.15,0:06:24.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're gonna be like that, bro{\fscx250}-{\fscx100}!
Dialogue: 6,0:06:24.17,0:06:26.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're gonna be like that, no matter how much time passes{\fscx250}-{\fscx100}
Dialogue: 6,0:06:26.32,0:06:28.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't wanna hear that from you.
Dialogue: 6,0:06:28.48,0:06:30.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just what do {\i1}you{\i0}  know about me?!
Dialogue: 6,0:06:30.71,0:06:31.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just a feeling.
Dialogue: 6,0:06:31.66,0:06:36.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've been wasting time on a park bench all Sunday.
Dialogue: 6,0:06:36.50,0:06:38.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's nothing a decent person would do.
Dialogue: 6,0:06:38.76,0:06:40.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was just{\fscx250}-{\fscx100}
Dialogue: 6,0:06:40.89,0:06:41.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was touring.
Dialogue: 6,0:06:41.96,0:06:44.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Touring? Awesome!
Dialogue: 6,0:06:45.62,0:06:47.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it was just on a bike.
Dialogue: 6,0:06:47.73,0:06:51.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Touring has to be on a motorcycle.
Dialogue: 6,0:06:51.69,0:06:53.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a pity. {that you're on a pedal-bike, not a motorcycle}
Dialogue: 6,0:06:53.21,0:06:56.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,School rules say that I can't get a license.
Dialogue: 6,0:06:57.36,0:06:59.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, motorcycles are pretty dangerous.
Dialogue: 6,0:06:59.89,0:07:01.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd rather have a car.
Dialogue: 6,0:07:02.52,0:07:04.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 6,0:07:04.05,0:07:07.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if you do it that way, you're fouring.
Dialogue: 6,0:07:07.92,0:07:11.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's making a pretty funny mistake about what "touring" means.
Dialogue: 6,0:07:17.62,0:07:20.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the roads here are really complex.
Dialogue: 6,0:07:20.54,0:07:24.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe you wanted to come here by yourself.
Dialogue: 6,0:07:24.39,0:07:26.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not my first time or anything.
Dialogue: 6,0:07:26.63,0:07:29.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Then why are you lost?
Dialogue: 6,0:07:31.13,0:07:32.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just been a while.
Dialogue: 6,0:07:33.42,0:07:36.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of which, Arararagi-san{\fscx250}-{\fscx100}
Dialogue: 6,0:07:36.26,0:07:37.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's one too many!
Dialogue: 6,0:07:37.83,0:07:39.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, I stuttered.
Dialogue: 6,0:07:39.27,0:07:41.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop stuttering and making things sound bad.
Dialogue: 6,0:07:42.69,0:07:44.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't help it!
Dialogue: 6,0:07:44.28,0:07:46.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone stutters.
Dialogue: 6,0:07:46.96,0:07:51.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or have you never stuttered in your life?
Dialogue: 6,0:07:51.32,0:07:52.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't say I haven't.
Dialogue: 6,0:07:53.08,0:07:55.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I almost never do it with people's names.
Dialogue: 6,0:07:55.82,0:07:56.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then.
Dialogue: 6,0:07:58.33,0:08:01.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say "bus gas explosion" three times.
Dialogue: 6,0:08:01.32,0:08:03.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not someone's name.
Dialogue: 6,0:08:03.00,0:08:06.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it is! I have like three friends named that!
Dialogue: 6,0:08:06.88,0:08:10.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So if anything, it's a common name!
Dialogue: 6,0:08:10.93,0:08:13.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bus gas explosion bus gas explosion bus gas explosion!
Dialogue: 6,0:08:13.97,0:08:15.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What animal eats dreams?
Dialogue: 6,0:08:16.74,0:08:17.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The tapir? 
Dialogue: 6,0:08:17.63,0:08:19.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bzzzt, wrong answer.
Dialogue: 6,0:08:19.68,0:08:21.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The animal that eats dreams is...
Dialogue: 6,0:08:23.26,0:08:24.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mankind.
Dialogue: 6,0:08:24.41,0:08:26.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not very clever!
Dialogue: 6,0:08:28.44,0:08:30.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Araragi-kun.
Dialogue: 6,0:08:31.15,0:08:33.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you give me the address again?
Dialogue: 6,0:08:33.78,0:08:35.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine, uhh.
Dialogue: 6,0:08:37.28,0:08:39.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seems like we went a little too far.
Dialogue: 6,0:08:39.83,0:08:40.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 6,0:08:40.96,0:08:43.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to blame me, go ahead and do it.
Dialogue: 6,0:08:43.20,0:08:46.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, there's nothing to blame you for.
Dialogue: 6,0:08:46.02,0:08:46.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 6,0:08:56.56,0:08:59.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you so scared of Senjougahara?
Dialogue: 6,0:09:00.63,0:09:03.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel like she hates me.
Dialogue: 6,0:09:03.30,0:09:07.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It feels like she thinks I'm in the way and she wants me to disappear.
Dialogue: 6,0:09:07.23,0:09:09.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't really think it's that extreme.
Dialogue: 6,0:09:11.43,0:09:13.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Senjougahara.
Dialogue: 6,0:09:13.11,0:09:14.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 6,0:09:14.16,0:09:15.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you hate kids?
Dialogue: 6,0:09:15.92,0:09:17.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hate them. I loathe them.
Dialogue: 6,0:09:17.87,0:09:19.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like it if they all died.
Dialogue: 6,0:09:20.72,0:09:23.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand how to connect with them.
Dialogue: 6,0:09:23.49,0:09:25.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It must have been back in middle school.
Dialogue: 6,0:09:25.66,0:09:30.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I went shopping at a department store, and ran into a kid who must have been around seven.
Dialogue: 6,0:09:30.80,0:09:32.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the kid started crying?
Dialogue: 6,0:09:32.84,0:09:34.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's not it.
Dialogue: 6,0:09:34.83,0:09:39.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I said to the seven-year-old:
Dialogue: 6,0:09:39.48,0:09:44.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Are you okay? Are you hurt at all? I'm sorry, I'm so sorry."
Dialogue: 6,0:09:45.39,0:09:49.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not knowing what to do with a kid, I lost my head.
Dialogue: 6,0:09:50.27,0:09:54.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But because of that, because I handled it so poorly...
Dialogue: 6,0:09:54.88,0:09:57.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It left me shocked.
Dialogue: 6,0:09:57.45,0:10:04.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From then on, whether they're human or not, I've hated kids.
Dialogue: 6,0:10:08.78,0:10:10.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, Araragi-kun.
Dialogue: 6,0:10:10.21,0:10:11.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 6,0:10:11.67,0:10:14.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think we've gone too far again.
Dialogue: 6,0:10:14.55,0:10:15.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The address?
Dialogue: 6,0:10:15.48,0:10:16.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, this has happened twice now.
Dialogue: 6,0:10:17.09,0:10:19.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to blame me, you can keep on blaming me.
Dialogue: 6,0:10:19.79,0:10:22.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's still nothing to blame you for.
Dialogue: 6,0:10:22.01,0:10:23.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, huh.
Dialogue: 6,0:10:23.47,0:10:27.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Senjougahara, isn't that line a little different from before?
Dialogue: 6,0:10:27.48,0:10:29.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh, I guess.
Dialogue: 6,0:10:29.07,0:10:30.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's up with that?
Dialogue: 6,0:10:30.01,0:10:33.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's right. You mentioned urban renewal. Maybe it's because of that?
Dialogue: 6,0:10:33.90,0:10:36.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's not it.
Dialogue: 6,0:10:36.66,0:10:39.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like the old roads are completely gone.
Dialogue: 6,0:10:39.84,0:10:42.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not actually lost. 
Dialogue: 6,0:10:43.40,0:10:44.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 6,0:10:44.84,0:10:48.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I'm gonna try using my GPS.
Dialogue: 6,0:10:54.02,0:10:55.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 6,0:10:57.09,0:10:59.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It suddenly went out of range. {note phone UI, lol}
Dialogue: 6,0:11:02.93,0:11:03.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 6,0:11:07.42,0:11:09.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess it's impossible.
Dialogue: 6,0:11:10.68,0:11:13.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because we can't get there no matter how many times we try.
Dialogue: 6,0:11:14.52,0:11:15.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hachikuji?
Dialogue: 6,0:11:16.59,0:11:19.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll never find my way there.
Dialogue: 6,0:11:19.62,0:11:22.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll never make it to where mommy is.
Dialogue: 6,0:11:23.97,0:11:28.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I'm a lost snail.
Dialogue: 6,0:11:48.81,0:11:51.95,Default,,0000,0000,0020,,Unable to reach our destination no matter what,
Dialogue: 6,0:11:51.95,0:11:53.90,Default,,0000,0000,0020,,we consulted Oshino.
Dialogue: 6,0:11:55.38,0:11:58.98,Default,,0000,0000,0020,,Do you know where it is? Maybe I should go.
Dialogue: 6,0:12:00.00,0:12:04.38,Default,,0000,0000,0020,,It doesn't make me happy that you're worried
Dialogue: 6,0:12:04.38,0:12:06.67,Default,,0000,0000,0020,,about my memory being as poor as yours.
Dialogue: 6,0:12:06.67,0:12:08.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If anything, it's enough to make me sad.
Dialogue: 6,0:12:09.30,0:12:10.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 6,0:12:11.83,0:12:12.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I mean...
Dialogue: 6,0:12:13.92,0:12:17.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't leave me alone with some kid.
Dialogue: 6,0:12:28.20,0:12:34.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Based on my conversation with Senjougahara, it seems like she has her guard up again.
Dialogue: 6,0:12:36.40,0:12:40.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mentioned your mom earlier, right?
Dialogue: 6,0:12:40.04,0:12:43.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you say Tsunade was a relative?
Dialogue: 6,0:12:44.78,0:12:50.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hachikuji-chan, I'll buy you ice cream later, so won't you come a little closer?
Dialogue: 6,0:12:52.48,0:12:53.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 6,0:12:54.30,0:12:58.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, about before. About your mom.
Dialogue: 6,0:12:59.67,0:13:01.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, mommy is a relative, right?
Dialogue: 6,0:13:02.11,0:13:04.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I guess.
Dialogue: 6,0:13:05.51,0:13:10.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And even if I call her mommy, it's sad because she's not mommy anymore.
Dialogue: 6,0:13:12.96,0:13:16.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsunade was my last name until third grade.
Dialogue: 6,0:13:16.83,0:13:21.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When daddy took me, I changed it to Hachikuji.
Dialogue: 6,0:13:21.02,0:13:27.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh man, and to think I told you to go visit your mom...
Dialogue: 6,0:13:27.03,0:13:31.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Naw, I'm not just going because it's Mother's Day.
Dialogue: 6,0:13:31.41,0:13:35.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can go to mommy's whenever I want.
Dialogue: 6,0:13:36.13,0:13:37.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 6,0:13:37.42,0:13:41.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But no matter how much I search, I never make it there.
Dialogue: 6,0:13:41.82,0:13:45.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then you met the snail?
Dialogue: 6,0:13:45.07,0:13:47.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know if we met, but...
Dialogue: 6,0:13:49.00,0:13:52.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must have had a lot of trouble.
Dialogue: 6,0:13:54.60,0:13:57.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Owww! What the hell are you doing, you brat!
Dialogue: 6,0:13:58.14,0:14:01.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ow! Ow! Ow, oww!
Dialogue: 6,0:14:24.94,0:14:27.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's nothing to laugh about.
Dialogue: 6,0:14:27.63,0:14:32.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From the second time on, victory is just hollow.
Dialogue: 6,0:14:33.80,0:14:38.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There stood a nihilistic high school boy who,
Dialogue: 6,0:14:38.57,0:14:42.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for the second time, smacked around a grade school girl until she blacked out.
Dialogue: 6,0:14:46.04,0:14:47.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By which I mean me.
Dialogue: 6,0:14:51.06,0:14:53.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You look scary, Araragi-kun.
Dialogue: 6,0:14:55.49,0:14:56.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hanekawa?
Dialogue: 6,0:14:56.58,0:14:59.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now you look surprised.
Dialogue: 6,0:15:00.08,0:15:02.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I guess that's an improvement.
Dialogue: 6,0:15:03.99,0:15:06.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's up? Why are you here?
Dialogue: 6,0:15:07.06,0:15:09.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just killing a little time.
Dialogue: 6,0:15:09.76,0:15:12.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh really?
Dialogue: 6,0:15:12.51,0:15:14.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm killing time too.
Dialogue: 6,0:15:14.57,0:15:18.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't like staying at home, so I go out for walks on Sunday.
Dialogue: 6,0:15:20.56,0:15:22.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think you're being too anxious.
Dialogue: 6,0:15:24.77,0:15:28.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, by the way, Araragi. Is that girl your little sister?
Dialogue: 6,0:15:28.73,0:15:30.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, she's a kid who got lost.
Dialogue: 6,0:15:30.96,0:15:33.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her name is Hachikuji Mayoi.
Dialogue: 6,0:15:33.07,0:15:37.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hachikuji? That's pretty common in Kansai.
Dialogue: 6,0:15:37.33,0:15:41.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I think of it, wasn't the temple in "Shinonome Monogatari"...
Dialogue: 6,0:15:42.53,0:15:44.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, wait, that was written differently.
Dialogue: 6,0:15:44.96,0:15:46.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know everything, don't you.
Dialogue: 6,0:15:47.07,0:15:50.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know everything, I just happen to know this.
Dialogue: 6,0:15:55.79,0:15:57.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hi there, Mayoi-chan.
Dialogue: 6,0:15:57.95,0:16:02.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm this guy's friend, Hanekawa Tsubasa.
Dialogue: 6,0:16:03.13,0:16:04.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't talk to me!
Dialogue: 6,0:16:04.93,0:16:06.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hate you!
Dialogue: 6,0:16:06.48,0:16:09.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh my, I did something she hates.
Dialogue: 6,0:16:10.24,0:16:11.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There, there.
Dialogue: 6,0:16:14.59,0:16:19.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're so cute, Mayoi-chan! I just want to eat you up!
Dialogue: 6,0:16:20.80,0:16:25.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you shouldn't suddenly bite his hand, okay?
Dialogue: 6,0:16:29.05,0:16:31.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, say sorry.
Dialogue: 6,0:16:33.50,0:16:35.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm sorry, Araragi-san.
Dialogue: 6,0:16:38.39,0:16:40.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And Araragi-kun, you shouldn't do that.
Dialogue: 6,0:16:40.85,0:16:43.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By "that", you mean... get violent, huh.
Dialogue: 6,0:16:43.52,0:16:46.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, you shouldn't be violent.
Dialogue: 6,0:16:46.43,0:16:53.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if you're going to spank a child, you need to tell them why so they understand.
Dialogue: 6,0:16:54.20,0:16:57.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Talking to you is really like studying.
Dialogue: 6,0:16:59.69,0:17:05.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So she's lost? Around here? If you'd like, I can show you around.
Dialogue: 6,0:17:06.45,0:17:10.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nah, I sent Senjougahara to find someone.
Dialogue: 6,0:17:10.45,0:17:13.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you were with her?
Dialogue: 6,0:17:16.09,0:17:22.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were asking me a lot about her before, weren't you.
Dialogue: 6,0:17:27.06,0:17:29.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's it! That's how it is!
Dialogue: 6,0:17:29.90,0:17:34.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, you can fantasize about those things even better than yaoi fangirls.
Dialogue: 6,0:17:34.15,0:17:35.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yaoi? What's that?
Dialogue: 6,0:17:36.15,0:17:39.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It stands for "no climax, no conclusion, deep meaning".
Dialogue: 6,0:17:39.24,0:17:42.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That sounds like a lie. I'll check it out later.
Dialogue: 6,0:17:42.83,0:17:43.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're so serious.
Dialogue: 6,0:17:43.96,0:17:47.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I'll just be in the way, so I'll get going now.
Dialogue: 6,0:17:47.62,0:17:50.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to bother you. Say hi to Senjougahara-san for me.
Dialogue: 6,0:17:50.96,0:17:53.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, that's a misunderstanding!
Dialogue: 6,0:17:53.72,0:17:57.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's right, Hanekawa. Can I ask you something?
Dialogue: 6,0:17:57.43,0:18:00.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know where someone named Tsunade-san lives around here?
Dialogue: 6,0:18:00.15,0:18:01.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsunade-san?
Dialogue: 6,0:18:02.72,0:18:03.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm...
Dialogue: 6,0:18:06.14,0:18:07.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't.
Dialogue: 6,0:18:07.76,0:18:10.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's something even you don't know?
Dialogue: 6,0:18:10.41,0:18:14.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't I tell you? I only know what I know.
Dialogue: 6,0:18:14.90,0:18:16.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anything else, not at all.
Dialogue: 6,0:18:16.61,0:18:17.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 6,0:18:18.04,0:18:20.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry I couldn't live up to your expectations.
Dialogue: 6,0:18:20.28,0:18:21.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No problem.
Dialogue: 6,0:18:21.36,0:18:23.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, bye-bye for real.
Dialogue: 6,0:18:30.97,0:18:34.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sunday, May 14th, at 14:15:30.
Dialogue: 6,0:18:34.51,0:18:37.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The moment I got Senjougahara's phone number.
Dialogue: 6,0:18:45.13,0:18:48.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh man, she's screwing up my Sunday morning slacking.
Dialogue: 6,0:18:48.96,0:18:50.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsundere-chan's such a mean girl.
Dialogue: 6,0:18:51.16,0:18:52.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsundere-chan?
Dialogue: 6,0:18:52.31,0:18:54.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you mean Senjougahara.
Dialogue: 6,0:18:54.20,0:19:00.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure have been running into a lot of oddities, Araragi-kun.
Dialogue: 6,0:19:00.70,0:19:02.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not the one who met it.
Dialogue: 6,0:19:03.75,0:19:05.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 6,0:19:05.04,0:19:08.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The one who met it is a girl named Hachikuji Mayoi.
Dialogue: 6,0:19:09.53,0:19:11.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Hachikuji Mayoi?
Dialogue: 6,0:19:12.14,0:19:15.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's how it is? I see, I see.
Dialogue: 6,0:19:15.75,0:19:19.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you say Hachikuji, you have to think of the fifth paragraph of "Shinonome Monogatari".
Dialogue: 6,0:19:20.08,0:19:22.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hanekawa said the same thing.
Dialogue: 6,0:19:22.97,0:19:24.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What?
Dialogue: 6,0:19:25.16,0:19:26.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Oshino?
Dialogue: 6,0:19:33.53,0:19:36.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're so unresourceful.
Dialogue: 6,0:19:37.40,0:19:38.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What're you talking about now?
Dialogue: 6,0:19:38.73,0:19:44.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Making Tsundere-chan take responsibility for this.
Dialogue: 6,0:19:44.20,0:19:48.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm sorry for dragging Senjougahara into this.
Dialogue: 6,0:19:48.95,0:19:51.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, I didn't mean it like that.
Dialogue: 6,0:19:51.44,0:20:00.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you being a bit optimistic thinking you can keep solving these oddities between you, her, and Class Rep-chan?
Dialogue: 6,0:20:00.24,0:20:02.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not what I'm trying to do.
Dialogue: 6,0:20:02.35,0:20:08.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I can't normally be by your side when you encounter oddities.
Dialogue: 6,0:20:08.19,0:20:11.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it's inconceivable that you could solve an incident over the phone.
Dialogue: 6,0:20:12.67,0:20:14.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I thought it'd be nothing.
Dialogue: 6,0:20:14.94,0:20:22.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I don't admire you sending a girl your age alone to the place where a weird guy lives.
Dialogue: 6,0:20:22.39,0:20:25.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you're not gonna do anything, are you?
Dialogue: 6,0:20:25.16,0:20:34.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm happy you trust me that much, but she doesn't.
Dialogue: 6,0:20:35.87,0:20:39.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't do anything! I won't do anything at all! Put down the stapler, Tsundere-chan!
Dialogue: 6,0:20:39.98,0:20:41.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stapler?
Dialogue: 6,0:20:42.05,0:20:43.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That scared me.
Dialogue: 6,0:20:43.73,0:20:46.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsundere-chan is pretty scary.
Dialogue: 6,0:20:46.62,0:20:48.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, uh.
Dialogue: 6,0:20:48.44,0:20:51.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I suck at the phone. It's hard to talk about.
Dialogue: 6,0:20:51.71,0:20:54.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hard to talk about... You mean...
Dialogue: 6,0:20:54.02,0:20:55.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, we'll do this.
Dialogue: 6,0:20:55.68,0:20:58.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell Tsundere-chan how to handle the lost cow.
Dialogue: 6,0:20:58.84,0:21:01.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You hang out there for a little bit, Araragi-kun.
Dialogue: 6,0:21:01.49,0:21:02.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Handle?
Dialogue: 6,0:21:02.64,0:21:04.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it okay to send the message through a person?
Dialogue: 6,0:21:04.61,0:21:09.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh... There won't be a ritual required like there was for Senjougahara?
Dialogue: 6,0:21:09.20,0:21:12.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope. Snails aren't as troublesome as crabs.
Dialogue: 6,0:21:12.31,0:21:18.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, it's not a god, more like a spirit or ghost.
Dialogue: 6,0:21:18.21,0:21:19.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Spirit?
Dialogue: 6,0:21:19.22,0:21:22.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Araragi-kun, you know.
Dialogue: 6,0:21:22.19,0:21:25.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Shikoku Pilgrimage, and the Kansai Kannon Pilgrimage.
Dialogue: 6,0:21:25.68,0:21:28.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, of course I know those.
Dialogue: 6,0:21:28.89,0:21:32.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hachikuji is one of those too.
Dialogue: 6,0:21:33.64,0:21:36.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, you see, you can read "Hachiku" as "Yaku".
Dialogue: 6,0:21:36.98,0:21:39.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So it can become misfortune. 
Dialogue: 6,0:21:39.61,0:21:44.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hachikuji was abandoned as that interpretation spread.
Dialogue: 6,0:21:46.28,0:21:49.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, now that you've been given the details and understand the history,
Dialogue: 6,0:21:49.65,0:21:52.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,what do you think when you look at the name Hachikuji Mayoi?
Dialogue: 6,0:21:53.23,0:21:56.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Normally you'd think it's an inconvenient name to have because of how much meaning it seems to carry.
Dialogue: 6,0:21:56.25,0:21:57.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How much meaning it seems to have?
Dialogue: 6,0:21:57.50,0:22:02.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would've been better if you had felt that at the beginning.
Dialogue: 6,0:22:02.62,0:22:04.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What would have been better about that?
Dialogue: 6,0:22:04.51,0:22:07.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, I'm gonna tell Tsundere-chan the details.
Dialogue: 6,0:22:08.77,0:22:13.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know if she'll tell you exactly what I said, but...
Dialogue: 6,0:22:17.19,0:22:19.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does he mean?
Dialogue: 6,0:22:21.78,0:22:25.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, Hachikuji, looks like something or other is going to happen.
Dialogue: 6,0:22:25.12,0:22:30.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That conversation didn't give me the impression that anything was going to happen at all.
Dialogue: 6,0:22:30.28,0:22:32.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, Araragi-san.
Dialogue: 6,0:22:32.24,0:22:33.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 6,0:22:34.65,0:22:36.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm hungry.
Dialogue: 6,0:24:10.73,0:24:11.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Karen!
Dialogue: 6,0:24:11.59,0:24:12.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Tsukihi!
Dialogue: 6,0:24:12.48,0:24:14.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, time for the preview quiz!
Dialogue: 6,0:24:13.36,0:24:14.08,Alt,,0000,0000,0000,,Quiz!
Dialogue: 6,0:24:14.08,0:24:15.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you mention catering{\fscx250}-{\fscx100}
Dialogue: 6,0:24:14.79,0:24:15.44,Alt,,0000,0000,0000,,Delivery!
Dialogue: 6,0:24:15.44,0:24:16.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like a cell phone!
Dialogue: 6,0:24:16.92,0:24:19.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not supposed to get catering on the train!
Dialogue: 6,0:24:18.76,0:24:19.73,Alt,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not supposed to!
Dialogue: 6,0:24:19.73,0:24:21.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time! Mayoi Snail, part 3!
Dialogue: 6,0:24:21.71,0:24:23.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can watch while catering, can't you?
Dialogue: 6,0:24:22.72,0:24:23.63,Alt,,0000,0000,0000,,1seg, I guess.
