Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.47,0:02:02.43,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1\c&H2A2EC4&\pos(1050,360)}spring break.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.43,0:02:03.22,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fs40\b1\pos(136,124)}I was assaulted by a vampire.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.22,0:02:03.89,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1\c&H2A2EC4&\pos(230,360)}By a
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.22,0:02:03.89,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1\c&H2A2EC4&\pos(1050,360)}beautiful beast.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.89,0:02:04.52,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fs40\b1\pos(64,85)}I was assaulted--By a beast beautiful enough to chill one's blood.\N\NAll the blood in my body--was wrung out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.52,0:02:05.06,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1\pos(230,360)\c&H8794ED&}As a result,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.52,0:02:05.06,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1\pos(1050,360)\c&H8794ED&}I became a vampire.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.06,0:02:05.56,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fs40\b1\pos(64,85)}The one who rescued me from that hell was\N\Nan older guy who was passing by, Oshino Meme.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.56,0:02:06.02,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1\pos(230,360)\c&H8794ED&}And I became
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.56,0:02:06.02,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1\pos(1050,360)\c&H8794ED&}human again.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.02,0:02:06.43,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs40\b1\pos(640,270)}Well, it's not that big of a deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.43,0:02:06.77,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1\pos(230,360)\c&H8794ED&}And it's nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.43,0:02:06.77,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1\pos(1050,360)\c&H8794ED&}all that wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.77,0:02:07.14,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1\an7\pos(68,59)\c&HE6F1FA&}It's over and done with.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.77,0:02:07.14,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&HE6F1FA&}{\b1\an7\pos(69,183)}The only remaining problem is that, if I continue drink blood monthly,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.77,0:02:07.14,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&HE6F1FA&}{\b1\an7\pos(74,308)}I have superhuman vision.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.77,0:02:07.14,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&HE6F1FA&}{\b1\an7\pos(73,431)}Since that's more like a trait,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.77,0:02:07.14,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&HE6F1FA&}{\b1\an7\pos(71,554)}I don't mind facing it for the rest of my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.14,0:02:07.44,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs50\b1\pos(642,638)\c&H51ACE7&}And--
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.44,0:02:07.73,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fs40\b1\pos(98,25)}I'm still lucky.\N\NAfter all, it all happened\N\Nduring spring break.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.73,0:02:07.98,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H5FB2E9&\b1\pos(210,360)}For example,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.73,0:02:07.98,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H5FB2E9&\b1\pos(1092,360)}Senjougahara\Nwas different.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.98,0:02:08.23,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fs40\b1\pos(98,25)\c&HE6F1FA&}For two years, she\N\Nheld something inconvenient within her.\N\NAn inconvenience that obstructed most of her free will.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.44,0:02:11.73,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1\an7\pos(127,26)\c&HD9DFF0&}Two years of that hell--I wonder how it felt.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.44,0:02:11.73,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1\an7\pos(126,120)\c&HD9DFF0&}Perhaps that's why Senjougahara uncharacteristically\Nfelt such a debt to me, or perhaps she had to--
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.44,0:02:11.73,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1\an7\pos(128,366)\c&HD9DFF0&}Leaving the inconvenience in her body aside... The fact that she was able to get rid\Nof the inconvenience in her heart was, perhaps, a very difficult result to obtain.
